text: Rebecca Murray (born 15 March 1990) is an American wheelchair basketball player. She won a gold medal at the 2008 Summer Paralympics, and 2012 Summer Paralympics. She played at the 2007 Parapan American Games, 2011 Parapan American Games, 2012 Summer Paralympics, 2014 Women's World Wheelchair Basketball Championship, 2015 Parapan American Games, and 2019 Parapan American Games. She was born in Milwaukee. She studied at Germantown High School in Germantown, Wisconsin. == References == Category:1990 births Category:Living people Category:Paralympic gold medalists for the United States Category:American wheelchair basketball players Category:Sportspeople from Milwaukee
